From: Super Z <super-z@local>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 12:34:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] =?UTF-8?q?feat(reasoning):=20v1.1=20=E2=80=94=20long-?=
 =?UTF-8?q?run=20engine=20+=20tool=20router?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Turns the agent from a per-turn synchronous loop into a long-running
autonomous worker that can run for hours/days without timeout, and
auto-selects the right tool for each task without explicit prompting.

== Long-Run Engine (agent/unified/longrun.py) ==
- Priority work queue with single worker thread (avoids concurrency
  issues with the non-thread-safe tool registry)
- CheckpointStore: JSONL append-only log at
  ~/.hermes/unified/longrun_checkpoint.jsonl. On restart, replays
  completed item_ids for idempotency — process crash mid-batch = pick
  up where left off
- ReflectionWorker: separate thread, debounced (5s default) + batched
  (10 items default per LLM call). Turns 50 reflections × 2s = 100s
  synchronous overhead into ~5 batches × 3s = 15s background work
  that never blocks the agent
- Heartbeat event every 30s for monitoring
- Fail-open everywhere: LLM failure drops reflection silently
- Stdlib only (threading, queue, json) — no asyncio rewrite needed

== Tool Router (agent/unified/tool_router.py) ==
- Indexes all tools from tools.registry (name, description, params,
  toolset, source)
- BM25 scoring against tokenized (name + description + params)
- 25 intent pattern boosts (read file, search, execute, web search,
  recall memory, plan, generate image, schedule, delegate, etc.)
- Usage learning: records which tools are actually called for which
  queries, boosts future suggestions (capped at +1.0 bonus)
- format_suggestions() renders <tool-suggestions> block for the
  system prompt — LLM sees relevant tools before generating tool call
- Complementary to existing tools/tool_search.py (which handles lazy
  loading); ToolRouter handles proactive suggestion

== Reasoning protocol updates ==
- ReasoningProtocol.reflect_batch(): single LLM call reflects on N
  items at once. Used by the background ReflectionWorker
- _parse_json_array() helper for batch JSON parsing

== Integration (agent/unified/integration.py) ==
- after_tool_call() now branches: if longrun_enabled, reflection goes
  to background worker; else synchronous (v1 behavior)
- configure_reasoning_stack() now also starts the long-run engine
  and wires reflect_batch_fn, if longrun.enabled
- New public API: suggest_tools_for_query(), record_tool_usage_for_message(),
  longrun_status(), enqueue_longrun_work(), shutdown_longrun()
- framework_status() exposes longrun_status + tool_router_stats

== Config (agent/unified/config.py) ==
- unified.longrun.enabled / heartbeat_seconds / reflection_debounce_seconds
  / reflection_batch_size
- unified.tool_router.enabled / top_n / learn
- Env overrides: HERMES_UNIFIED_LONGRUN, HERMES_UNIFIED_TOOL_ROUTER

== Smoke tests ==
- ToolRouter: 5 queries, all return relevant tools. Usage learning
  verified (grep boosted after 3 uses for 'search' queries)
- LongRunEngine: priority queue (CRITICAL→HIGH→NORMAL), idempotency
  (re-enqueue skipped), checkpoint persistence, 5 reflections batched
  into 1 LLM call after debounce
- reflect_batch: 3 items → 1 LLM call → 3 results. Empty/No-LLM
  edge cases verified

All new behavior opt-in (default OFF). Legacy behavior unchanged.
See docs/REASONING_DESIGN.md Part II for full design.
